What is FastAPI?

FastAPI is a modern Python backend framework built for:

High performance
Async APIs
Scalability
Type safety
Automatic validation
Modern cloud-native systems

It is built on top of:
    Starlette → web handling
    Pydantic → validation & serialization
and runs on:
    ASGI
    async/await
    event loop architecture
FastAPI solved:
    ✅ speed
    ✅ async support
    ✅ automatic validation
    ✅ developer productivity
    ✅ type safety
    ✅ scalability

Core Advantages of FastAPI
    1. Extremely Fast Performance

            FastAPI is one of the fastest Python frameworks.

            Performance close to:

            Node.js
            Go

            because it uses:
                ASGI
                async I/O
                non-blocking architecture
        Why FastAPI is Fast

            Traditional frameworks use:
                Request → Block worker → Wait → Response
            FastAPI uses:
                Request → await → worker free → process other requests

            This dramatically improves concurrency.
    2. Native Async Support

        FastAPI was designed for async from day one.

        Example:
            @app.get("/")
            async def get_data():
                data = await db.fetch()
                return data

            While waiting for DB:

                server handles other requests

        This is huge for modern systems.

        Async is excellent for:
            DB calls
            Redis
            Kafka
            RabbitMQ
            external APIs
            cloud services
            streaming
    3. Automatic Validation

        This is one of FastAPI’s biggest strengths.
            Using Pydantic:
                from pydantic import BaseModel

                class User(BaseModel):
                    name: str
                    age: int

            FastAPI automatically validates:

                ✅ missing fields
                ✅ wrong types
                ✅ invalid data
    4. Automatic API Documentation

        FastAPI auto-generates:
            Swagger UI
            OpenAPI docs
            ReDoc
        /docs
        /redoc

        Benefits
        Frontend teams can:
            test APIs instantly
            understand schemas
            avoid manual docs
    5. Type Hints = Safer Code

        FastAPI deeply uses Python type hints.

        Example:
            async def get_user(id: int):

            Benefits:
                ✅ IDE autocomplete
                ✅ static analysis
                ✅ fewer bugs
                ✅ better maintainability
    6. Dependency Injection System

            FastAPI has powerful dependency injection.

            Example:
                def get_db():
                    return db

                @app.get("/")
                def route(db = Depends(get_db)):

            Useful for:
                DB sessions
                authentication
                logging
                caching
                permissions
    7. Better Developer Productivity

            FastAPI reduces boilerplate.

            Compared to older frameworks:
                less code
                cleaner APIs
                automatic serialization
                automatic validation
            Example
                Returning Python dict:
                    return {"message": "hello"}
                FastAPI automatically converts to JSON.

    8. Excellent for Microservices

        FastAPI is lightweight and modular.

        Perfect for:
            cloud-native systems
            Kubernetes
            Docker
            distributed systems
    9. WebSocket Support

            FastAPI supports real-time communication.

            Examples:

            chat apps
            stock market
            gaming
            live tracking
    10. Easy Integration with Modern Systems

        FastAPI integrates beautifully with:
            | Tool         | Purpose       |
            | ------------ | ------------- |
            | Redis        | caching       |
            | Apache Kafka | streaming     |
            | RabbitMQ     | task queues   |
            | PostgreSQL   | database      |
            | Docker       | containers    |
            | Kubernetes   | orchestration |


How FastAPI Offers Speed

    Deep Internal Architecture

    Step 1 — Uvicorn Receives Request

        Uvicorn accepts HTTP request.

    Step 2 — ASGI Event Loop

        ASGI event loop manages concurrent requests.

        Unlike threads:

            One event loop handles many waiting operations
    Step 3 — Async Processing

        When route hits:

            await db.fetch()

            request pauses WITHOUT blocking server.

    Step 4 — Event Loop Switches Tasks

        Server processes other requests meanwhile.

    This is the key performance advantage.

