4.    In MySQL if we want to have cluster — if one goes down, other can serve — how many instances do we need?

        Minimum 2 instances are required for failover (1 primary + 1 replica), but for a reliable and production-ready cluster, at least 3 instances are recommended to achieve quorum and avoid split-brain issues.

        Minimum Setup
            1.Two Instances (Basic Failover)

            1 Primary (Master)
            1 Replica (Slave)

            ✔ Works for basic failover
            ✖ Problem: Split-brain risk (no quorum / tie-breaker)
            ✖ Failover often manual or needs external tool

        Recommended Setup (Production)

            2. Three Instances (Best Practice)

            1 Primary

            2 Replicas

            OR in cluster-based systems:

            3 nodes total

            ✔ Provides quorum (majority voting)
            ✔ Avoids split-brain problem
            ✔ Enables automatic failover
