5.    Let’s say I am trying to protect DB by username & password — how to do it in Flask without secret manager?
        Instead of using secret manager We can store the credentials using .env file then we can load these into the application without hard-coding in source code.

        if we store secrets in source code:
            Any one can able to see whoever is accessing the bitbucket
            unsafe if repo becomes public
            It may get committed to git
        use .env file for reading the secrets from it and load using python-dotenv package for local development.
